~ SYNOPSIS :
        - The script is mainly used to send one or many attachements as an email. for your desired purposes.

~ PYTHON VERSION : PYTHON 3.5

~ PYTHON PACKAGES :
        import smtplib
        from os.path import basename
        from email.mime.application import MIMEApplication
        from email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart
        from email.mime.text import MIMEText
        from email.utils import COMMASPACE, formatdate


~ SCRIPT NAME : Attachment_Emailer.py

~ USAGE :
        - send_from     - should be a scalar value (CAN BE SET WITH A DEFAULT VALUE).
        - send_to       - can be list, tuple or join of strings by COMMA (CAN BE SET WITH A DEFAULT VALUE).
        - subject       - should be a scalar value (CAN BE SET WITH A DEFAULT VALUE).
        - text          - The Body of the email is set here.
        - files         - The total files that are going to be sent.
        - server        - should be set based on requirement, should be authenticated if the email should not be sent to spam or
                          it should be white listed. (CAN BE SET WITH A DEFAULT VALUE).
